latestIgtvVideos.caption:
Color Fix Extravaganzaaa!!!! My first video y’all, she’s just getting started okay go easy on her! @danessa_myricks you inspire me to be a better, more creative, thoughtful makeup artist, I’m so inspired by you!! Thank you for creating such iconic beauty and for makeup products that have taken my own artistry to new heights! If there were one makeup product I would choose to spend the rest of my mua life with it would be color fix!! Literally could not think of a product that would allow me to create the lewks I envision so effortlessly! The impact, the color pay off, the blend ability, the staying power! Just divine! And don’t even get me started on vision cover cream... lol thank you @danessa_myricks for the ascension you have brought to the mua community! Definitely channeling you for this lewk with the glossy lid💜💜💜💜💜💜💜
.
.
.

latestPosts.caption:
✍️ @therealspenceradkins The last time I spoke with Andrew Dahling, the club kid diva from Boone County, his partnership as makeup artist to Chappell Roan was just beginning to take flight. Having done Roan’s makeup at Governor’s Ball, Bonnaroo, The Tonight Show, and the Kentuckiana Pride Festival, Dahling’s career was at a tipping point. Since then, he’s been as busy as ever painting the Midwest Princess an showing out at Bartschland in New York City. “It’s been kind of a whirlwind,” Dahling said of the past year.⁠
⁠
“Yeah, the MTV VMAs [Video Music Awards] happened, and that was wild.” He recalls, “I guess you have this perspective based off of being the viewer—the fan, the spectator—and then you’re behind the scenes. It’s just very surreal, all these people walking around, doing their thing, working the stage.”⁠
⁠
"THE SHOW MUST GO ON" is ALL about performance. 💃 Performance shows up in the lives of Queer people every day. We perform through our crafts, like drag and art. Or we perform for the world as loud activists fighting back. Or we perform by code-switching while navigating fear and oppression. And we are weary of the performances of our allies…are they authentic in their support or is it simply….performance? Yet, no matter the stage or the role, the Queer experience never breaks, and the show must go on.⁠
⁠
👯‍♂️ Join Queer Kentucky for their latest print edition featuring original stories, gorgeous photography, and exclusive interviews with Zack Wickham of Bravo’s The Valley, award-winning singer SG Goodman, and Chappell Roan’s makeup artist Andrew Dahling.⁠
